{bold}CONCLUSIONS{nobold}
{pp}
During the time I played Hell Squad I found it rather enjoying. The game is not going to win the Academy Award for being the most amazing one on the market, but can easily steal some of the hours of your free time.{p}
The graphics are not amazing. The use of low resolution is, in a way a limitation, but the cartoony colours can make up for that.{p}
The sound is OK although a spoken dialogue would have been nice and the control system function pretty well, even if you just use a keyboard although I found the gun aiming system, at times, not very precise.{p}
Overall, it is not the prettiest kid in the block but a good effort which should be rewarded by buying the game now.
